reviewBlob: I love RABC!!  Which is why I tried this Brewers Cut #0002 Belgian Quadrupel. Id drank other Belgian beers in the past & found them pretty good.  But I couldnt even get past the first bottle of this stuff. :( Syrupy taste isnt my idea of beer. Almost like they poured in lots of caramel sugar or just plain corn syrup.  I wont be buying any more of this...though as I said, I love RABC despite this mistake (IMHO) on their part.
beerName: Real Ale Brewers Cut Black Quad

reviewBlob: Other than Samuel Smiths Taddy Porter (Yorkshire, UK), this Porter by RABC is the FINEST Ive run across, though its exceeded by a slim margin by RABCs Coffee Porter which unfortunately is "seasonal". Wish they had it year-round. Nevertheless, this RABC Brewers Cut #3 Porter is right up there with the very best! :)
beerName: Real Ale Brewers Cut Dry-Hopped Porter

reviewBlob: Excellent Brown Ale, very much like some of the fine "Scottish Brown Ale" that Ive drank. RABC does this one right as well! :)
An outstanding Porter.  RABC is without question the BEST brewer in TX and one of the finest in the USA! They do it RIGHT!! :)
beerName: Real Ale Barrel Aged Coffee Porter

reviewBlob: Best Porter (which is my favorite type of brew; no "lite" stuff for me!) Ive ever drank! Rather hard to find unless youre in one of the larger metro areas. :( Wish one could order this wonderful Porter online!
